    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="126"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/167.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chairman of the Central Committee of the <gloss type="to">American National
                            Red Cross</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Receipt is acknowledged of your letter of
                    December 19, 1914, giving the views of the Red Cross on the proposed advance of
                    $5,000,000 on the Huai River loan.</p>
                <p>Pursuant to the suggestion of the Central Committee of the Red Cross, the
                    Department sent a telegram to the American Minister at Peking on December 22,
                    1914, a paraphrase of which is herewith enclosed for your information, setting
                    forth the views of the Committee on the loan.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
